  "body": "tracking https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/pull/2466/commits/713a7bd2c481222f556c32d16d925a3b6aa4fc10#r722816358\r\n\r\nSince the locations of immutables are statically known (no matter what value they are set to), we can insert symbols into the LLL which directly precede blank space. Basically, _sym_foo doesn't actually take any space in the code. So the runtime data section itself would have something like\r\n```\r\n_sym_datasection_start\r\nBLANK\r\n_sym_immutable_uint256\r\nJUMPDEST... <32 JUMPDESTs>\r\n_sym_immutable_bytes6\r\nJUMPDEST... <32+6 jumpdests>\r\n```\r\nThen the code for copying items to LLL would stay the same (it would just overwrite all the jumpdests), but we would know the locations statically.",
